21:33.267 --> 21:39.474
And as the disciples are kind of coming back to Jesus with these answers, he's like, well, how about you?

21:40.194 --> 21:43.840
This is the question that he asks in Matthew chapter 16 verse 15.

21:45.682 --> 21:49.749
But you Jesus asked them, who do you say that I am?

21:49.809 --> 21:57.180
Simon Peter answered, you are the Messiah, the son of the living God.

21:58.382 --> 22:05.292
Jesus responded, blessed are you Simon son of Jonah, because flesh and blood did not reveal this to you, but my father in heaven.

22:07.095 --> 22:09.138
We see this is the first time Peter

22:10.562 --> 22:12.265
reveals this to Jesus.

22:12.285 --> 22:14.127
He's like, I believe this about you.

22:15.169 --> 22:21.358
And his profession revealed his faith that he believed that he was the one that Jewish people had been waiting for.

22:21.378 --> 22:22.940
And I love the response that Jesus gives him.

22:22.960 --> 22:24.062
He says, blessed are you.

22:25.925 --> 22:27.347
You didn't work to earn that.

22:27.808 --> 22:30.051
You didn't white knuckle your way into that understanding.

22:30.492 --> 22:32.475
It pleased God to reveal that to you.

22:33.837 --> 22:35.099
He showed you the truth of this.

22:36.961 --> 22:40.146
Christmas is the time that we celebrate that God came near.

22:41.250 --> 22:46.456
that he entered creation and he made a way for us to know him and experience him.

22:48.519 --> 22:59.392
But if you talk with people in your life, family, friends, coworkers, about what Christmas means or about who Jesus is, they may give you a variety of answers.

23:00.894 --> 23:02.416
Yeah, Jesus, he was a good moral teacher.

23:03.958 --> 23:04.879
He was a great guy.

23:06.141 --> 23:07.543
Or, you know what, I don't really care.

23:07.563 --> 23:10.386
I don't really think about it very much.

23:11.234 --> 23:14.379
But that question, it is front and center for us, every Christmas.

23:15.360 --> 23:16.382
Who is Jesus?

23:17.384 --> 23:17.664
Really?

23:17.684 --> 23:19.988
C.S.

23:20.128 --> 23:22.211
Lewis is an author and professor.

23:22.251 --> 23:24.735
He was writing back in the time of World War II.

23:25.216 --> 23:28.922
And he often heard this same answer from people about who Jesus was.

23:28.962 --> 23:31.005
But then he wrote this in his book, Mirror Christianity.

23:31.566 --> 23:36.613
I'm trying here to prevent anyone saying the really foolish thing that people often say about him.

23:37.034 --> 23:39.538
I'm ready to accept Jesus as a great moral teacher.

23:39.746 --> 23:41.789
but I don't accept his claim to be God.

23:43.350 --> 23:45.273
That is one thing we must not say.

23:46.274 --> 23:49.598
A man who said the sort of thing Jesus said would not be a great moral teacher.

23:50.439 --> 23:58.169
He'd either be a lunatic on a level with a man who says he's a poached egg or else he would be the devil of hell.

23:59.650 --> 24:00.832
You must make your choice.

24:01.933 --> 24:06.619
Either this man was and is the son of God or else a madman or something worse.

24:07.620 --> 24:09.042
You can shut him up for a fool

24:09.762 --> 24:17.930
You can spit at him and kill him as a demon, or you can fall at his feet and call him Lord and God.

24:18.931 --> 24:22.895
But let us not come with any patronizing nonsense about his being a great human teacher.

24:22.975 --> 24:24.617
He's not left that open to us.

24:25.698 --> 24:26.959
He did not intend to.

24:28.961 --> 24:35.888
As we spend time over the next seven weeks opening the scripture together, our hope is that we would see Jesus for who he truly is.

24:36.248 --> 24:38.450
He was not just a moral teacher.

24:39.618 --> 24:43.125
He was not just a good person, although he was those things.

24:43.165 --> 24:43.566
He was.

24:45.129 --> 24:46.232
He was more than that.

24:47.254 --> 24:48.657
He was the Son of God.

24:50.300 --> 24:51.001
It is through him.

24:51.042 --> 24:55.310
He is the only way that we can know and experience who God is.

24:55.350 --> 24:56.413
It's through faith in him.

24:56.733 --> 24:59.058
And that is what Christmas is about.

25:01.026 --> 25:04.471
as we continue to discover more and more about Jesus in this series together.

25:04.491 --> 25:10.961
Not only are we gonna grow in our understanding, but we're gonna need to take this understanding and this knowledge, and we're going to need to apply it.

25:12.163 --> 25:15.868
We're gonna need to answer the question of why does this matter for me?

25:17.371 --> 25:19.213
How is this gonna change how I live?

25:19.273 --> 25:23.139
How does knowing this about Jesus impact my life today?

25:25.102 --> 25:26.544
Well, I have two answers to that question.

25:28.287 --> 25:30.290
Because Jesus is the Son of God,

25:31.010 --> 25:34.394
That means that God's plans never fail.

25:36.256 --> 25:37.137
God is sovereign.

25:38.098 --> 25:40.861
It was God's perfect plan to send us a Savior.

25:40.921 --> 25:42.022
It wasn't plan B.

25:43.523 --> 25:47.147
It wasn't plan C. God was like, oh, we got to figure something else out.

25:47.167 --> 25:48.549
No, this was His plan.

25:49.590 --> 25:50.831
Nothing could get in the way of it.

25:51.772 --> 25:54.375
And that is true for everything God intends to do.

25:55.797 --> 26:00.882
The sovereignty of God is this beautiful doctrine that means that nothing in your life happens.

26:01.154 --> 26:05.178
outside of his understanding, outside of his control.

26:05.238 --> 26:13.305
This is especially encouraging for us because there's so many times in our life where we think, if only I was in control.

26:13.365 --> 26:25.697
If only I could change this, situations where you just don't know the outcome, times of worry and stress, times where you do anything, just be like, I'm gonna make this happen.

26:27.779 --> 26:30.962
God knows of those situations more deeply

26:31.138 --> 26:32.640
then you're even experiencing them.

26:33.782 --> 26:37.668
And he knows what you need, and he'll provide you with what you need.

26:38.729 --> 26:40.331
God's plans never fail.

26:40.432 --> 26:43.536
We see that in his plan to send us Jesus.

26:45.759 --> 26:48.343
Second thing, why does this matter for us?

26:49.264 --> 26:55.033
Well, because Jesus is the Son of God, that means we can clearly know and understand what God is like.

26:56.415 --> 26:58.578
God is not a mystery to us.

26:59.106 --> 27:03.050
John 1 18, the one and only son has revealed him.

27:05.653 --> 27:07.095
We don't have to wonder about God.

27:07.175 --> 27:12.260
So many people wonder and they're like, well, I'm going to look for it in these signs or these other places.

27:13.241 --> 27:14.503
We don't have to do that.

27:15.584 --> 27:21.610
We've been given a clear record of who he is in a way that we can experience him in this life.

27:23.052 --> 27:24.914
It's through Jesus.

27:25.826 --> 27:31.292
The Son of God, Romans chapter 10, verse 9 and 11, this is the letter that Paul wrote to the Roman church.

27:32.093 --> 27:38.681
If you confess with your mouth, Jesus is Lord, and if you believe in your heart that God raised them from the dead, you will be saved.

27:39.161 --> 27:39.782
That's what it is.

27:40.963 --> 27:47.511
One believes with the heart resulting in righteousness, and one confesses with the mouth, resulting in salvation.

27:49.613 --> 27:53.778
When this happens in a person, when they confess and believe,

27:54.754 --> 27:55.815
They become a Christian.

27:56.836 --> 28:00.661
The Holy Spirit moves into their life and begins to change them.

28:01.481 --> 28:05.105
They begin to experience joy and forgiveness from sin in this life.

28:06.948 --> 28:15.957
And I'm so excited because today, in our service, we're gonna celebrate that reality with people who are getting baptized.

28:17.139 --> 28:23.666
You know, some who have heard the truth of the gospel and who have believed it, that Jesus lived a perfect life for them.

28:24.130 --> 28:27.194
that he died on the cross for them, that he rose from the dead for them.

28:27.234 --> 28:32.562
Every single person that's getting baptized here today, they've become Christians.

28:33.543 --> 28:38.490
Some of them have done so very recently and they're getting baptized and some have been walking with Jesus for years.

28:39.251 --> 28:41.394
And now we're saying, I wanna get baptized.

28:42.656 --> 28:47.483
But what baptism is, it's an outward demonstration of an inward reality.

28:49.345 --> 28:52.850
The scripture is clear that if you follow Jesus, you should get baptized.

28:53.218 --> 29:08.014
It's an act of obedience that people are taking to show the world that they belong to Him, that their lives are no longer about themselves, but that they trust in the work that Jesus has done for them, that they're forgiven of their sin, and they have new life in Christ.

29:09.736 --> 29:13.520
As people get baptized today, it's a picture of that very truth that they'll be witnessing.

29:14.401 --> 29:22.450
As people are immersed down in the water, it symbolizes their old life being buried, and as they come out

29:23.042 --> 29:25.965
It's symbolizing the new life they have in Christ.

29:28.247 --> 29:32.491
What comes into your mind when you think about God is the most important thing about you.

29:34.853 --> 29:37.095
What comes into your mind when you think about Jesus?

29:38.997 --> 29:49.307
If it's that He is the Son of God, the one who has come to make a way for you to know and experience God, choose to follow Him.

29:49.347 --> 29:53.010
Trust Him with your life.

29:54.594 --> 30:09.688
You know, if that's already true for you today as a Christian, you can rest in knowing that God's plans never fail, that he is sovereign, that he's good, that the Christmas story was plan A to send us a Savior.

30:11.950 --> 30:20.098
And if you are a follower of Jesus today and you've not taken the step of obedience and baptism, I wanna encourage you, do it.

30:21.359 --> 30:22.560
Don't put it off any longer.

30:23.221 --> 30:24.242
Get baptized.

30:24.354 --> 30:32.106
Today, don't wait to grow more in your faith or you have all the reasons I get it, but look, you can get baptized today.

30:32.126 --> 30:35.571
To get baptized means you follow Jesus.

30:36.212 --> 30:37.134
Stop, that's it.

30:38.416 --> 30:41.560
We have clothes, we have towels, we have shorts for you.

30:41.581 --> 30:43.704
You don't have to get baptized in your Sunday best.

30:43.724 --> 30:46.148
You can, if you want, you don't have to though.

30:47.590 --> 30:50.354
But if that's you, if you're hearing thinking, I want to get baptized.

30:50.562 --> 30:52.024
I follow Jesus, I've never done it.

30:52.304 --> 30:53.205
I wanna get baptized.

30:53.506 --> 30:58.251
I wanna encourage you after I pray here in just a moment, you can go and talk with Ellen in the info center.

30:58.312 --> 31:03.157
She'd love to have a conversation with you about your faith, about your decision to get baptized today.

31:04.559 --> 31:06.361
But in just a moment, we're gonna sing some more.

31:06.401 --> 31:10.026
And we're gonna celebrate for the rest of our time this morning.

31:10.046 --> 31:19.858
And as we do so, let us do that looking at Jesus, the Son of God, and be grateful for that life that we have in Him.

31:20.930 --> 31:21.331
Let's pray.

31:21.491 --> 31:22.873
Heavenly Father, I do just thank you.

31:25.297 --> 31:26.278
God, I thank you for Christmas.

31:29.263 --> 31:36.113
God, in our greatest need, you gave us yourself that you entered creation.

31:38.998 --> 31:49.554
God, it's crazy thinking that everything in the world was created through Jesus, that he's eternal, that he showed up in the world like us.

31:51.618 --> 31:52.299
as a baby.

31:54.581 --> 32:21.330
God, that encourages me so much because it just helps us remember that God, when when your plans and your will with all of that Lord, nothing can get in the way or that you are good and that your love was seen for us most clearly in the Christmas story and sending us Emmanuel.

32:21.794 --> 32:24.962
a Savior, our Messiah, the Son of God.

32:25.002 --> 32:35.246
We thank you so much for Jesus, and we're so excited to celebrate this morning, people who have chosen to follow Him and who have given their lives to Him in faith.

32:37.692 --> 32:38.875
It's in Jesus' name that we pray.

32:39.937 --> 32:40.338
Amen.

